	doi = {10.1177/107327481502200314},
	abstract = {BACKGROUND: Advances in technology have pushed the boundaries of neurosurgery. Surgeons play a major role in the neurosurgical field, but robotic systems challenge the current status quo. Robotic-assisted surgery has revolutionized several surgical fields, yet robotic-assisted neurosurgery is limited by available technology.
METHODS: The literature on the current robotic systems in neurosurgery and the challenges and compromises of robotic design are reviewed and discussed.
